Unless you're ordering food That you are able to see them pour onto the plate in the front part of the restaurant Do Not order food that they have to give you from the back.   The food here smells amazing- And that's what gets you through the door but you soon realize when you place your order that they're giving you reheated food from the back.   Anything involving pork shoulder ( pernil) is not fresh.   The rice is constantly being reheated they don't make fresh rice and if they do that's not what they're going to serve you.  With these folks you're safe with eating any stewed meats, hot soup, rotisserie chicken things that are up against the glass that are being cooked right in front of you.  Thumbs down.

I spent 22 dollars and the food was horrible, the mangu was hard and cold, the egg was rubbery, close to fake Fisher price eggs, the salami was burnt and the longaneza was dry. Not only did the staff have a bad it's too early to be up and serving people attitude, the food appearance was poor. I bought the food trying not to judge, giving it a chance but nope. I won't ever waste my money there again. A breakfast special here where I live is $5.00 that include mangu and the tres gorpes, its freshly made not just sitting there under the lamp drying up. The morir soñando small is $3 they charged 5 and it was nasty, sugary and sour. I don't like to criticize people but rest assured this is being done with hope's that if I ever have to go back there to eat, they fixed their butts and poor quality of services and food, providing better friendly services and the food is fresher. At the least take this and make it a better experience for future customers that's if you're still open for business.... To be honest I'm surprised you've stay open this long if you're serving food like the one I sadly ate with regret to say no, I don't want it... Next time I'll just turn away and follow my gut feeling especially after seeing the food appearance and highly over charging for the food, only if I could give credit for great taste at the least, but damn not even that will help them win it.

I've been here a few times and I have to say, I really enjoy the food. My favorite go-to dish is the stewed chicken with rice and beans and plantain. The chicken has tons of flavor. The plantains can sometimes be hit or miss. I've gotten them sometimes when they were pretty dry. Otherwise, I think you get a great deal for your money. They typically pack a lot of the food in the container and I almost never can finish it all in one sitting. Just a quick tip, a lot of the staff dont speak English very well, so if you don't speak Spanish, get comfortable with pointing to what you want. But the staff are super friendly and helpful. Looking forward to my next meal there. The only thing that doesnt land this place at a 5 for me is that they advertise delivery and when I called to place an order the guy there said they didnt offer delivery. I highly recommend that they change their menu and signage if they don't actually deliver.
